"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:10.5.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">10.5.4</span> 標題：項鏈、鏈、帶子（necklace, chain, cord）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Aramaic</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">蘭：הַמְנִיךְ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： hamnik)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:16\">DAN 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:16\">DAN 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29\">DAN 5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29\">DAN 5:29</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חָרוּז</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： charuzim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:10\">SNG 1:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： כּוּמָז</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： kumaz)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:22\">EXO 35:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： נְטִיפָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： netifah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:26\">JDG 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:19\">ISA 3:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： עֲנָק, ענק</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ‘anaq（名詞或動詞）)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:26\">JDG 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:6\">PSA 73:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:9\">PRO 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:9\">SNG 4:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： פָּתִיל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： pathil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:25\">GEN 38:25</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： רָבִיד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ravid)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:42\">GEN 41:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:11\">EZK 16:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שַׂהֲרוֹן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： saharonim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:26\">JDG 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:18\">ISA 3:18</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： μανιάκης</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： maniakēs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd3:6\">1ES 3:6</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0533_necklace.jpg\" alt=\"項鍊\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">項鍊 (© Wolfgang Sauber, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>項鏈是戴在脖子上作為裝飾的帶子、繩子或鏈子，通常串著珠寶或其他飾物。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:42\">GEN 41:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:16\">DAN 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29\">DAN 5:29</a> ：在這些經文中，掌權者把金鏈賜給被擢升到高位的人。在這兩處經文中，鏈子可能比普通的項鏈更粗更結實，因此最好用一個意指「鏈」而非裝飾性細項鏈的詞。不過，重要的是要在譯文中表明榮譽或高位之意，而非奴役。在一些語言中，有特定的詞語來指稱戴在脖子上、代表榮譽或高位的物件。如果沒有這樣的詞語或詞語意思模糊，那麽可以通過展開譯文來表達榮譽的意思，例如，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 將<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a> 譯為“chain of honor”（「榮譽的鏈子」）。</p>\n<p>根據一些解經家的意見，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:16\">DAN 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29\">DAN 5:29</a> 中的亞蘭文<em>hamnik</em> 實際上並不是指鏈子，而是指一種不會變形的金屬項圈。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 譯為“collar”（「項圈」）。在有些語言中，可以用一個動詞來表示穿紫色衣服和戴金項圈這兩種權柄的象徵。但在另一些語言中，用兩個動詞來分別表示「穿」衣服和「戴」鏈子或項圈等飾物，會更自然一些。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:10\">SNG 1:10</a> ：希伯來文<em>charuz</em> （複數，<em>charuzim</em> ）實際上指帶孔的小珠子或寶石。用帶子把這些小珠子或寶石串起來，就成了一條項鏈。有些譯本把<em>charuzim</em> 譯為「項鏈」（“necklaces”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr> 、PV ），有些譯本則譯成做項鏈所用的「珠寶」（“jewels”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> ）或「寶石」。還有些譯本結合了這兩種譯法：<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 譯為“strings of jewels”（「珠寶串」），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Standard Bible\">NASB</abbr> 譯為“strings of beads”（「珠串」），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 譯為“necklace of precious stones”（「寶石項鏈」），而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Spanish Common Language Version (Dios Habla Hoy)\">SPCL</abbr> 譯為「珍珠項鏈」。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:22\">EXO 35:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a> 中，希伯來文<em>kumaz</em> 的意思不確定，但顯然是指某種珠寶。大多數譯本都認為這是戴在脖子上的物品，可能是「項鏈」（“necklaces”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> ）或「吊墜」（“pendants”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr> ）。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:25\">GEN 38:25</a> ：在這兩節經文中，希伯來文<em>pathil</em> 可能指一種戴在脖子上的帶子，用來掛印戒。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 將<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:25\">EXO 30:25</a> 中的這個詞譯成“cord around your neck”（「戴在脖子上的帶子」），這個譯法很好。</p>\n<p>關於希伯來文<em>netifah</em> 和<em>saharonim</em> ，參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">10.5 珠寶、首飾、飾物 (jewelry, ornaments)&lt;REALIA:10.5&gt;</a> 就<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:18-Isa3:23\">ISA 3:18–ISA 3:23</a> 所做的討論。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
